            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>97</offset>
                <text>At examination he showed no dysmorphic features and had a normal gait.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>168</offset>
                <text>Initially, it was thought that his symptoms were caused by traumas, as he practiced kickboxing as a hobby.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>275</offset>
                <text>Radiologically, in retrospect, the typical, symmetrical, cortical thickening of the diaphysis of the lower extremities was observed (Fig. 2).</text>
                <annotation id="8">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0005791</infon>
                    <location length="36" offset="57"/>
                    <text>cortical thickening of the diaphysis</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>417</offset>
                <text>He also showed sclerosis of the metacarpalia of the left hand.</text>
                <annotation id="9">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0006174</infon>
                    <location length="29" offset="15"/>
                    <text>sclerosis of the metacarpalia</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>480</offset>
                <text>The presence of radiologically confirmed bone abnormalities in the proposita (Fig. 1) as well as in her son (Fig. 2) suggested an autosomal dominant inheritance pattern.</text>
                <annotation id="10">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0011842</infon>
                    <location length="18" offset="41"/>
                    <text>bone abnormalities</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>650</offset>
                <text>Consequently, we could rule out melorheostosis (which are mostly sporadic cases) as well as van Buchem’s disease (autosomal recessive inheritance) as possible diagnoses.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>820</offset>
                <text>This led us to the diagnosis of Camurati–Engelmann Disease (CED).</text>
            </sentence>
        </passage>
